title: Statement from the Mexican Embassy regarding Felipe Solis | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House




April 27, 2009

 



Statement from the Mexican Embassy regarding Felipe Solis




 THE WHITE HOUSE Office of the Press Secretary   For Immediate Release  April 27, 2009  Statement from Ricardo Alday, Spokesman for the Mexican Embassy to the United States of America:  "Mr. Felipe Solís, Director of Mexico’s National Anthropology Museum died on April 23rd, a week after he welcomed Presidents Obama and Calderón at the Museum. He died of complications of a preexisting condition and not of swine flu." THE WHITE HOUSE, April 27, 2009.
